item.title: How can i be sure does i have been PORTFOWARDED CORRECTLY ! None Anzwers yet :Z
item.dc:creator: @Random666 Random666
item.description:
@Random666 wrote:

Don’t change the port 113 to 43594, thats different. You’ve already port-forwarded. Maybe you haven’t changed your firewall settings. Open up your network connections and where it says local area connection right click and click properties. Go to advanced and click settings. Go to the exeptions tab and add port. Put name as anything and port as 43594. Done. Also make sure you have no-ip DUC running and signed in
